# Version Management

## Version Format

`MAJOR.MINOR.BUILD.REVISION` — e.g. `0.0.0.1`, `1.0.0.0`, `1.2.3.45`

| Part | When to increment |
|------|------------------|
| MAJOR | Breaking change / incompatible API |
| MINOR | New feature, backwards-compatible |
| BUILD | Bug fix |
| REVISION | Internal/patch |

## plcproj Version

Set in `.plcproj` `<PropertyGroup>`:

```xml
<ProjectVersion>0.0.0.1</ProjectVersion>
```

## Global_Version GVL

Create `GVLs/Global_Version.TcGVL` with `ST_LibVersion` from `Tc2_System`:

```iecst
{attribute 'TcGenerated'}
VAR_GLOBAL CONSTANT
    stLibVersion : ST_LibVersion := (
        iMajor    := 0,
        iMinor    := 0,
        iBuild    := 0,
        iRevision := 1,
        sVersion  := '0.0.0.1'
    );
END_VAR
```

`ST_LibVersion` is defined in `Tc2_System`. Reference it for runtime version queries.

## Project Folder Convention

```
Versions/
  0.0.0.1/
    changelog-0.0.0.1.md
  1.0.0.0/
    changelog-1.0.0.0.md
```

## Changelog Format

Keep changelogs short and in English. One file per release version.

```markdown
# Changelog vX.Y.Z.R

## New Features
- FB_Example: brief description of what it does

## Data Structures (DUTs)
- ST_Example_Data: fields and purpose
- E_Example_State: enum states

## Bug Fixes
- Fixed: description of fix

## Breaking Changes
- Renamed: OldName → NewName
```

Rules:
- English only
- List every new FB, DUT, GVL, and Helper Function
- Note breaking changes explicitly
- No implementation details — purpose only
